<Base title="Privacy Notice | Peptide Atlas" description="What information the Peptide Atlas network processes, why it is used, and the choices available to visitors." currentSection="" showDisclaimer={false}>
  <article>
    <p class="eyebrow">Effective July 22, 2026</p>
    <h1>Privacy notice</h1>
    <p>This notice covers the Peptide Atlas network: mypeptide.club, toppeptideslist.com, safepeptides.us, peptidesnews.us, and peptidesupdates.com.</p>
    <h2>Information we process</h2>
    <p>The sites do not offer user accounts, treatment intake, purchases, or comment forms. Our hosting provider may process ordinary technical logs such as IP address, browser and device information, requested pages, timestamps, and security events to deliver, protect, and troubleshoot the sites.</p>
    <p>If privacy-focused audience measurement is enabled, we use it to understand aggregate page visits and improve the network. We do not use advertising trackers or build profiles for targeted advertising. If you email us, we receive your address, message, and any information you choose to include.</p>
    <p>Directory pages use professional and business information from public clinic websites and official records. Correction requests are reviewed against the cited source record.</p>
    <h2>How information is used and shared</h2>
    <p>Information is used to operate and secure the sites, measure reliability, answer messages, investigate corrections, and maintain accurate publications. Service providers may process limited information on our behalf for hosting, security, email, and audience measurement. We do not sell personal information or share it for cross-context behavioral advertising.</p>
    <h2>Health information</h2>
    <p>Peptide Atlas is an information publisher, not a healthcare provider or patient portal. Do not send medical records, insurance details, government identification numbers, or other sensitive health information. If such material is received unexpectedly, we will limit access and delete it when it is no longer needed to address the request.</p>
    <h2>Retention, choices, and rights</h2>
    <p>We keep correspondence and operational records only as long as reasonably needed for the purposes above, security, dispute handling, and legal obligations. You may ask about, correct, or request deletion of personal information you provided, subject to applicable exceptions. Use the <a href="/corrections/">corrections page</a> for directory information or the <a href="/security/">security page</a> for security matters.</p>
    <h2>Children and changes</h2>
    <p>The network is intended for a general adult audience and is not directed to children under 13. We may update this notice as the services change. A revised notice will show a new effective date on this page.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
